01:26:06,896 --> 01:26:09,421
- What?
- Hey.

981
01:26:12,234 --> 01:26:18,244
You remember...? You remember
that woman with the dead dog?

982
01:27:20,337 --> 01:27:22,305
We drained it.

983
01:27:40,289 --> 01:27:42,154
Where's the boy?

984
01:27:42,324 --> 01:27:45,528
He wasn't home, thank God.
He was at his grandparents'.

985
01:27:45,529 --> 01:27:47,326
That's good.

986
01:27:47,963 --> 01:27:49,625
That's good.

987
01:29:04,373 --> 01:29:08,243
The remains will be shipped this afternoon.
Check the address of the funeral home.

988
01:29:08,244 --> 01:29:09,478
That's correct.

989
01:29:09,479 --> 01:29:14,685
If I can be of any other help,
just let me know.

990
01:30:17,980 --> 01:30:19,005
Sir?

991
01:30:23,153 --> 01:30:25,884
You got any jumper cables?

992
01:30:34,997 --> 01:30:36,465
Thanks.

993
01:30:40,403 --> 01:30:45,673
I wanted to say how sorry I am
for what happened to Mike.

994
01:30:45,675 --> 01:30:51,046
And I wanted to apologize for lying
about not seeing him that night.

995
01:30:51,046 --> 01:30:58,515
I just thought that if I were Mike,
I wouldn't want my parents to know.

996
01:30:59,221 --> 01:31:02,382
- You got a cigarette?
- Yeah.

997
01:31:20,342 --> 01:31:23,246
You think Bonner killed him?

998
01:31:24,780 --> 01:31:26,338
No.

999
01:31:27,583 --> 01:31:29,381
I don't know.

1000
01:31:31,253 --> 01:31:34,556
I don't understand any of this.

1001
01:31:35,792 --> 01:31:37,792
What would he have against my boy?

1002
01:31:37,793 --> 01:31:39,386
Nothing.

1003
01:31:41,230 --> 01:31:42,755
I'm sorry.

1004
01:31:45,935 --> 01:31:49,805
- Mike tell you much about Bosnia?
- Some.

1005
01:31:49,805 --> 01:31:56,377
We seemed to always pull sentry duty
together. Freezing our asses off.

1006
01:31:56,378 --> 01:31:58,479
He tried to convince me
of crazy things.

1007
01:31:58,480 --> 01:32:00,615
Try to get you to wear pantyhose?

1008
01:32:00,617 --> 01:32:02,751
- Did he tell you?
- No, I told him.

1009
01:32:02,752 --> 01:32:06,069
Cuts the cold like nothing else.

1010
01:32:06,422 --> 01:32:07,989
So he wasn't lying?

1011
01:32:07,990 --> 01:32:16,203
You don't want to get shot wearing
a pair of those. You'll never live it down.

1012
01:32:35,952 --> 01:32:38,319
It's fucked up, isn't it?

1013
01:32:38,320 --> 01:32:39,787
Yeah.

1014
01:33:04,980 --> 01:33:07,181
Let's get you to a good
American hospital.

1015
01:33:07,182 --> 01:33:09,885
Come on, speed this thing up!

1016
01:33:09,886 --> 01:33:13,173
It's okay. I'm gonna help you.

1017
01:33:13,789 --> 01:33:15,858
It's okay. Take it easy.

1018
01:33:15,859 --> 01:33:19,577
We're gonna take care of you, okay?

1019
01:33:22,698 --> 01:33:25,257
You okay? You all right?

1020
01:33:26,101 --> 01:33:29,921
Now, where does it hurt? Right there?

1021
01:33:30,640 --> 01:33:32,801
Easy. Right there?

1022
01:33:33,208 --> 01:33:36,926
We're gonna take care of you, okay?

1023
01:34:13,615 --> 01:34:15,048
Good night.

1024
01:35:14,143 --> 01:35:18,779
Tell me that's your son's signature
on his credit-card receipt.

1025
01:35:18,780 --> 01:35:20,771
No, it is not.

1026
01:35:21,184 --> 01:35:23,918
We always assumed Mike was there.

1027
01:35:23,920 --> 01:35:26,320
That's Penning's signature.

1028
01:35:26,322 --> 01:35:30,155
Three meals. Penning, Bonner and Long.

1029
01:36:05,962 --> 01:36:09,230
Penning and Long. I want them now.

1030
01:36:09,231 --> 01:36:14,536
- I can't give them to you.
- Oh, yes, you can. And you will.

1031
01:36:14,537 --> 01:36:17,072
Corporal Penning has come forward.

1032
01:36:17,073 --> 01:36:20,390
He's implicated Long and Bonner.

1033
01:36:20,743 --> 01:36:22,872
You son of a bitch.

1034
01:36:23,011 --> 01:36:25,913
You went to him with a fucking deal,
didn't you?

1035
01:36:25,914 --> 01:36:29,917
- He'll do serious time.
- Yeah? How serious, huh?

1036
01:36:29,918 --> 01:36:32,786
How serious? How much time?

1037
01:36:33,722 --> 01:36:36,266
As much as I could get.

1038
01:36:37,859 --> 01:36:40,194
Well, luckily for me, that means shit.

1039
01:36:40,195 --> 01:36:42,863
You see these? Those are warrants.

1040
01:36:42,864 --> 01:36:46,268
We have jurisdiction,
you're compelled to deliver those men.

1041
01:36:46,269 --> 01:36:48,069
I want them now.

1042
01:36:49,372 --> 01:36:53,274
I am not the only one who made a deal.

1043
01:36:53,275 --> 01:36:55,844
My C.O. Talked to yours.

1044
01:36:55,845 --> 01:36:59,820
It is just one less headache for them.

1045
01:37:00,048 --> 01:37:02,216
It's out of our hands now.

1046
01:37:02,217 --> 01:37:03,742
I'm sorry.

1047
01:37:05,621 --> 01:37:07,248
I bet you are.

1048
01:37:10,726 --> 01:37:12,828
I wanna hear the confession.

1049
01:37:12,828 --> 01:37:15,564
Long isn't speaking.
I'll get you Penning's statement.

1050
01:37:15,564 --> 01:37:19,400
No, I wanna hear it from his lips,
and I want him present.

1051
01:37:19,402 --> 01:37:21,961
That's not gonna happen.

1052
01:37:25,041 --> 01:37:27,842
How many soldiers
leave this base every night...

1053
01:37:27,844 --> 01:37:30,244
...to go visit a bar, have a drink or two?

1054
01:37:30,246 --> 01:37:33,814
- I know you're feeling burned.
- I'm not burned, I'm fucking pissed off.

1055
01:37:33,815 --> 01:37:37,652
Take a guess. On an average weekend,
what, seven, eight thousand soldiers?

1056
01:37:37,653 --> 01:37:41,122
You know what? I'm gonna sit in my car
outside any of your entrances...

1057
01:37:41,123 --> 01:37:44,225
...and pull over every vehicle
that comes back to this base...

1058
01:37:44,226 --> 01:37:49,331
...and I will arrest every soldier whose blood
alcohol is 1/1000 over the legal limit.

1059
01:37:49,332 --> 01:37:52,634
- How many men would that be?
- And how long till you're fired?

1060
01:37:52,635 --> 01:37:55,503
I'll do it on my own time,
and we have a good union...

1061
01:37:55,505 --> 01:37:58,105
...so I'm gonna say four to five weeks.

1062
01:37:58,106 --> 01:38:03,078
How many DUI's do you think
I could make in a month?

1063
01:38:03,078 --> 01:38:05,136
Should we find out?

1064
01:38:23,666 --> 01:38:25,634
Commander's office.

1065
01:38:25,635 --> 01:38:31,773
- Let me speak to Captain Henning, please.
- One moment, sir.

1066
01:38:31,774 --> 01:38:33,641
We were leaving the strip club.

1067
01:38:33,643 --> 01:38:36,478
And we thought that Mike and Bonner
have cooled down.

1068
01:38:36,479 --> 01:38:40,481
They could be like that,
laughing one minute and fighting the next.

1069
01:38:40,483 --> 01:38:43,318
Anyway, we're in the car,
and Mike's all pissy...

1070
01:38:43,319 --> 01:38:46,555
...and Bonner just starts needling him.

1071
01:38:46,555 --> 01:38:48,489
Just saying shit.

1072
01:38:48,658 --> 01:38:50,319
Like what?

1073
01:38:50,525 --> 01:38:54,395
I don't know.
Like what a good driver Mike is.

1074
01:38:54,396 --> 01:38:56,497
Stuff that makes no sense.

1075
01:38:56,498 --> 01:38:58,733
But Bonner has enough,
and he pulls over...

1076
01:38:58,734 --> 01:39:02,636
...and they just start
going off on each other.

1077
01:39:02,637 --> 01:39:06,240
And Long was yelling for them
to cut it out so we can go home.

1078
01:39:06,242 --> 01:39:09,077
And Mike starts cussing at him too...

1079
01:39:09,078 --> 01:39:13,347
...and then I look down,
and I'm stabbing him.

1080
01:39:13,349 --> 01:39:15,283
You...? You are?

1081
01:39:16,152 --> 01:39:17,551
Yeah.

1082
01:39:20,422 --> 01:39:22,823
And your friends didn't try and stop you?

1083
01:39:22,824 --> 01:39:26,386
I think they were sort of stunned.

1084
01:39:26,761 --> 01:39:28,363
They're yelling.

1085
01:39:28,363 --> 01:39:33,083
And Mike falls to the ground,
and he's dead.

1086
01:39:33,235 --> 01:39:38,557
And Long is screaming,
"Christ, what do we do now?"

1087
01:39:38,940 --> 01:39:42,444
It was Bonner's idea to chop him up.

1088
01:39:42,444 --> 01:39:45,180
He used to work for a butcher.

1089
01:39:45,180 --> 01:39:50,585
He knew how to work the knife
around the joints. Made it easier.

1090
01:39:50,586 --> 01:39:53,421
We would've buried the parts...

1091
01:39:53,421 --> 01:39:58,399
...but it was getting late
and we hadn't eaten.

1092
01:39:59,028 --> 01:40:00,962
You were hungry?

1093
01:40:01,130 --> 01:40:02,688
Starving.

1094
01:40:04,699 --> 01:40:08,018
We stopped at the Chicken Shack.

1095
01:40:09,971 --> 01:40:12,688
I liked Mike, we all did.

1096
01:40:13,809 --> 01:40:21,783
But I think on another night that would've
been Mike with the knife and me in the field.

1097
01:40:21,783 --> 01:40:24,914
I think he was the smart one.

1098
01:40:26,322 --> 01:40:28,622
I think he could see.

1099
01:40:32,595 --> 01:40:34,895
I'm truly sorry, sir.

1100
01:40:36,431 --> 01:40:39,061
I'm sorry for your loss.

1101
01:40:48,677 --> 01:40:51,279
I saw a video Mike shot.

1102
01:40:51,279 --> 01:40:54,324
Him in the back of a Humvee.

1103
01:40:57,453 --> 01:41:02,117
Looked like he was
torturing a prisoner or...

1104
01:41:07,296 --> 01:41:11,595
We arrested some haji who was wounded.

1105
01:41:12,835 --> 01:41:15,652
And we were riding along...

1106
01:41:15,738 --> 01:41:18,672
...and Mike was pretending
like he was a medic.

1107
01:41:18,673 --> 01:41:23,877
And he would stick his hand
in this guy's wound...

1108
01:41:23,878 --> 01:41:26,680
...and he says, "Does this hurt?"

1109
01:41:26,681 --> 01:41:30,344
And the haji screamed, "Yeah, yeah."

1110
01:41:30,987 --> 01:41:34,823
And then Mike would stick his hand
in the exact same place...

1111
01:41:34,823 --> 01:41:37,813
...and say, "Does that hurt?"

1112
01:41:41,796 --> 01:41:43,940
It was pretty funny.

1113
01:41:47,069 --> 01:41:50,042
It became a thing with Mike.

1114
01:41:51,740 --> 01:41:55,287
That's how he got the name "Doc."

1115
01:41:56,244 --> 01:41:59,118
It was just a way to cope.

1116
01:42:00,015 --> 01:42:02,661
We all did stupid things.

1117
01:42:45,728 --> 01:42:47,719
Excuse me, sir.

1118
01:43:06,114 --> 01:43:10,262
You know where Private Ortiez's room is?

1119
01:43:18,860 --> 01:43:20,747
You got a minute?

1120
01:43:23,498 --> 01:43:25,966
I need to apologize to you.

1121
01:43:25,967 --> 01:43:28,302
You got some real serious issues, man.

1122
01:43:28,304 --> 01:43:29,793
Yeah.

1123
01:43:31,673 --> 01:43:33,301
That's true.

1124
01:43:45,520 --> 01:43:50,057
I got a honorable discharge,
if you could believe it.

1125
01:43:50,059 --> 01:43:53,948
It's the Army, I'll believe anything.

1126
01:43:54,630 --> 01:43:57,016
I hated it over there.

1127
01:43:57,032 --> 01:44:00,301
Sleep in fucking tents.
No toilets, no showers.

1128
01:44:00,301 --> 01:44:04,121
No toilet paper, gotta use your hand.

1129
01:44:04,340 --> 01:44:07,298
I couldn't wait to get out.

1130
01:44:08,877 --> 01:44:11,279
After two weeks here...

1131
01:44:13,349 --> 01:44:16,479
...all I wanna do is go back.

1132
01:44:18,186 --> 01:44:20,279
How fucked is that?

1133
01:44:30,332 --> 01:44:32,719
You know what that is?

1134
01:44:36,505 --> 01:44:39,039
Mike took it and e-mailed it to me.

1135
01:44:39,041 --> 01:44:41,341
Why would he do that?

1136
01:44:48,216 --> 01:44:52,177
I don't know what anybody's told you.

1137
01:44:52,854 --> 01:44:55,088
There are standing orders.

1138
01:44:55,090 --> 01:44:56,890
You're in a convoy...

1139
01:44:56,891 --> 01:45:00,094
...someone or something gets in front
of you, you do not stop.

1140
01:45:00,095 --> 01:45:06,404
You stop, shitheads pop up
with RPG's and kill you all dead.

1141
01:45:18,380 --> 01:45:20,939
First week in Iraq...

1142
01:45:21,283 --> 01:45:23,851
...we're driving downrange.

1143
01:45:23,853 --> 01:45:26,054
Six of us in the back.

1144
01:45:26,055 --> 01:45:29,358
You can't see squat back there.

1145
01:45:30,960 --> 01:45:32,951
Doc hit something.

1146
01:45:34,762 --> 01:45:38,338
We hear it thump around underneath.

1147
01:45:39,667 --> 01:45:41,430
He stops.

1148
01:45:41,604 --> 01:45:43,332
Gets out.

1149
01:45:44,506 --> 01:45:46,337
Drives on.

1150
01:45:48,476 --> 01:45:50,206
Not a word.

1151
01:45:52,780 --> 01:45:55,182
Later, some guy said...

1152
01:45:55,251 --> 01:45:57,115
...we hit a kid.

1153
01:45:57,653 --> 01:45:59,782
I don't believe it.

1154
01:45:59,921 --> 01:46:01,947
You ask me...

1155
01:46:03,958 --> 01:46:05,823
...we hit a dog.

1156
01:46:07,930 --> 01:46:10,023
We killed a dog.

1157
01:46:13,534 --> 01:46:16,408
I don't know what that is.

1158
01:46:18,640 --> 01:46:20,699
No fucking idea.

1159
01:46:46,402 --> 01:46:49,804
Hey, Bonner, there's your family.

1160
01:46:49,805 --> 01:46:52,172
- Stop fucking around!
- It's a fucking phone.

1161
01:46:52,173 --> 01:46:55,009
- You could have broken it.
- You're a fucking idiot.

1162
01:46:55,010 --> 01:46:56,065
Oh, fuck.

1163
01:46:56,979 --> 01:46:59,514
- Oh, shit.
- Do not stop! Do not fucking stop!

1164
01:46:59,515 --> 01:47:03,490
- What do I do?
- Speed up! Speed up!

1165
01:47:10,859 --> 01:47:13,360
- What are you doing?
- Dad?

1166
01:47:13,362 --> 01:47:16,096
Get back in the fucking vehicle, Mike!

1167
01:47:16,097 --> 01:47:19,266
Mike, get back in the fucking vehicle!

1168
01:47:19,268 --> 01:47:20,701
Daddy?

1169
01:47:28,077 --> 01:47:31,136
Let's go, Mike, now!

1170
01:47:31,913 --> 01:47:34,144
Are you there, Daddy?

1171
01:47:34,750 --> 01:47:37,136
I can hardly hear you.

1172
01:47:38,619 --> 01:47:41,751
You gotta get me out of here.

1173
01:47:42,457 --> 01:47:45,862
Well, that's just nerves talking.

1174
01:47:47,363 --> 01:47:49,854
Something happened, Dad.

1175
01:47:59,041 --> 01:48:01,012
For Christ's sake.

1176
01:48:03,945 --> 01:48:06,676
Is anybody there with you?

1177
01:48:08,417 --> 01:48:10,045
No, I'm alone.

1178
01:48:13,622 --> 01:48:15,145
That's good.

1179
01:48:16,992 --> 01:48:19,789
Okay, Daddy, I gotta go.

1180
01:48:21,997 --> 01:48:23,896
You be safe, son.

1181
01:48:24,065 --> 01:48:25,795
Stay safe.

1182
01:48:27,168 --> 01:48:30,002
Yeah. You too.

1183
01:48:59,134 --> 01:49:03,503
You know, my son's been driving me crazy
ever since you came over.

1184
01:49:03,505 --> 01:49:05,769
He wants a slingshot.

1185
01:49:10,311 --> 01:49:14,945
Guess it could be worse.
Could be a BB gun.

1186
01:49:40,676 --> 01:49:41,818
Thank you.

1187
01:51:34,088 --> 01:51:37,658
So every day,
Goliath would walk into the valley...

1188
01:51:37,658 --> 01:51:41,185
...to challenge someone, anyone.

1189
01:51:41,863 --> 01:51:44,751
But no one would fight him.

1190
01:51:44,800 --> 01:51:47,167
Until David showed up...

1191
01:51:47,168 --> 01:51:50,171
...and said, "You know what?
I'll do it. I'll fight him."

1192
01:51:50,171 --> 01:51:54,175
So the king dressed David up
in his own armor, which was so big...

1193
01:51:54,176 --> 01:51:58,309
But why would he let him fight a giant?

1194
01:51:58,512 --> 01:52:00,555
He was just a boy.

1195
01:52:03,284 --> 01:52:05,930
I don't know, sweetheart.

1196
01:52:07,389 --> 01:52:10,277
Do you think he was scared?

1197
01:52:10,759 --> 01:52:11,783
David?

1198
01:52:17,733 --> 01:52:19,359
Yeah.

1199
01:52:19,667 --> 01:52:23,902
I think he would have been really scared.

1200
01:53:13,721 --> 01:53:16,756
- Just like that?
- Just like that.

1201
01:53:16,757 --> 01:53:18,902
It looks really old.

1202
01:53:19,694 --> 01:53:21,909
It's been well used.

1203
01:53:32,239 --> 01:53:34,274
And I shouldn't take it down at night?

1204
01:53:34,275 --> 01:53:35,833
No.

1205
01:53:37,445 --> 01:53:40,420
You leave it just like that.

1206
01:53:41,248 --> 01:53:43,463
That's a lot easier.
